  <body>
    <section name="SchemaCrawler - Chain Example">
      <subsection name="Description">
        <p>SchemaCrawler allows scripting with database
          metadata, using JavaScript. This example shows how to "chain" or run
          multiple SchemaCrawler commands.
        </p>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="How to Run">
        <ol>
          <li>
            Make sure that
            <span class="code">java</span>
            is on your
            <span class="code">PATH</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            Start the database server by running the
            <span class="code">StartDatabaseServer</span>
            script from the
            distribution directory
          </li>
          <li>
            Start a command shell in the
            <span class="code">chain</span>
            example directory
          </li>
          <li>
            Run
            <span class="code">chain.cmd chain.js
            </span>
            (or
            <span class="code">chain.sh chain.js
            </span>
            on
            Unix)
          </li>
        </ol>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="How to Experiment">
        <ol>
          <li>
            Try modifying the JavaScript in the
            <span class="code">chain.js
            </span>
            file
            to run different SchemaCrawler commands.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </subsection>
    </section>
  </body>
</document>
